    <!-- SCIENCE SECTION -->
    <h2 id="science">The Neuroscience of Focus: How Nootropic Ingredients Work</h2>

    <p>Understanding how focus gummies work requires a brief tour of the neurochemistry behind sustained attention. Concentration is not a single brain state — it involves the coordinated activity of multiple neurotransmitter systems, brain wave patterns, and neural network connections working in concert.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Alpha waves (8-12 Hz)</strong>
        <p>The brain's "focused calm" frequency. Dominant during sustained attention, reading, and creative problem-solving. L-theanine promotes alpha waves within 30-40 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Acetylcholine</strong>
        <p>The primary neurotransmitter for learning and memory. Alpha-GPC crosses the blood-brain barrier and provides the choline building block for acetylcholine synthesis.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Nerve Growth Factor (NGF)</strong>
        <p>A protein essential for neuron survival and new neural connections. Lion's mane stimulates NGF synthesis, supporting long-term neuroplasticity and cognitive resilience.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>BDNF</strong>
        <p>Brain-Derived Neurotrophic Factor supports neuron growth and synaptic plasticity. Coffee cherry extract (NeuroFactor) has shown acute BDNF increases of 143% in pilot studies.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>L-Theanine: The Alpha Wave Promoter</h3>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A 2019 study in <em>Nutrients</em> measured EEG brain wave activity in <strong>30 healthy adults</strong> after 200mg L-theanine ingestion. Alpha wave power increased significantly within <strong>40 minutes</strong> — with the effect persisting for over 2 hours. Participants reported improved subjective attention without any sedation or drowsiness.</p>
      <cite>Nutrients, 2019 — 30 participants, EEG-measured</cite>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A 2021 systematic review in <em>Plant Foods for Human Nutrition</em> analyzed <strong>9 randomized controlled trials</strong> and concluded that L-theanine at 200mg significantly improves attention and reduces anxiety across diverse populations, including high-stress individuals and those with mild cognitive challenges.</p>
      <cite>Plant Foods for Human Nutrition, 2021 — 9 RCTs</cite>
    </div>

    <h3>The L-Theanine + Caffeine Synergy</h3>

    <div class="vs-strip">
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>L-Theanine Alone</strong>
        <p>Promotes alpha waves, reduces anxiety, improves sustained attention. No stimulant effect.<br /><em>Nutrients, 2019</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Caffeine Alone</strong>
        <p>Blocks adenosine receptors, increases alertness. Can cause jitters, anxiety, and energy crashes.<br /><em>General pharmacology</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Combined (200mg + 100mg)</strong>
        <p>Improved speed and accuracy of attention tasks beyond either alone. Caffeine's jitters eliminated.<br /><em>Nutritional Neuroscience, 2008</em></p>
      </div>
      <div class="vs-item">
        <strong>Optimal Ratio</strong>
        <p>2:1 L-theanine to caffeine. 200mg L-theanine + 100mg caffeine = one focus gummy + one cup of coffee.<br /><em>Published consensus, 2008-2021</em></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- HOW WE TESTED -->
    <div class="tested-box">
      <h3>How We Tested These Focus Gummies</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Purchased independently.</strong> Every product was bought at full retail price through Amazon or brand websites. No brand was informed of this evaluation or provided free product.</li>
        <li><strong>Verified ingredient doses.</strong> We reviewed supplement facts panels and contacted manufacturers to confirm individual ingredient amounts. Products using proprietary blends that obscure doses were penalized in our transparency scoring.</li>
        <li><strong>Evaluated clinical evidence.</strong> Each active ingredient was cross-referenced against published peer-reviewed research. We prioritized products using ingredients at their clinically studied doses rather than underdosed amounts.</li>
        <li><strong>Assessed third-party testing.</strong> We requested certificates of analysis from each brand. Products with USP, NSF, or independent lab verification received higher quality scores than self-tested brands.</li>
        <li><strong>Conducted a focus session test.</strong> Four team members used each product during a standardized 90-minute work session, rating subjective focus, clarity, and sustained attention on a 1-10 scale. Results were averaged alongside objective ingredient analysis.</li>
        <li><strong>Calculated long-term value.</strong> Cost per serving was computed at retail price. Products offering 30+ servings with clinical-dose ingredients received the highest value ratings.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h2 id="who-should-take">Who Should Consider Focus Gummies?</h2>

    <p>Nootropic focus gummies are most appropriate for adults seeking non-stimulant cognitive support for sustained concentration, mental clarity, and long-term brain health. Based on the ingredient evidence and our testing, these groups benefit most:</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Knowledge workers and students</strong>
        <p>Anyone who needs sustained concentration for reading, writing, coding, or studying will benefit from L-theanine's alpha wave promotion and the calm focus it produces.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Caffeine-sensitive individuals</strong>
        <p>If coffee causes anxiety, jitters, or sleep disruption, focus gummies offer cognitive support through non-stimulant pathways that do not interfere with sleep architecture.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>Adults 40+ seeking neuroprotection</strong>
        <p>Lion's mane and phosphatidylserine support long-term brain health through NGF stimulation and neuronal membrane maintenance — proactive cognitive preservation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <strong>High-stress professionals</strong>
        <p>Stress hormones (cortisol) directly impair prefrontal cortex function — the brain region responsible for focus. Adaptogens like ashwagandha and L-theanine counteract this.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Who should exercise caution:</strong> Individuals taking prescription nootropics, ADHD medications, or antidepressants — some ingredients may interact with these drugs. Pregnant or breastfeeding women should avoid nootropic supplements due to insufficient safety data. People with mushroom allergies should avoid lion's mane products. If you take blood thinners, consult your physician before using supplements containing Gotu Kola.</p>
    </div>

