    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Focus Gummies</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Do focus gummies actually work?</summary>
      <p>The effectiveness of focus gummies depends entirely on the active ingredients and their dosages. Compounds like L-theanine (200mg), lion's mane extract (500mg+), and alpha-GPC (300mg) have published clinical evidence supporting cognitive benefits. A 2019 study in <em>Nutrients</em> found that 200mg L-theanine increased alpha brain wave activity within 40 minutes — alpha waves are associated with calm, focused attention. However, many focus gummies contain underdosed ingredients or proprietary blends that obscure actual amounts. Look for products that disclose individual ingredient doses and use clinically studied amounts.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the best ingredient for focus gummies?</summary>
      <p>L-theanine is the most evidence-backed focus ingredient available in gummy form. It promotes alpha brain wave production, which is associated with the relaxed-but-alert mental state optimal for sustained concentration. A 2021 systematic review in <em>Plant Foods for Human Nutrition</em> analyzed 9 RCTs and confirmed that L-theanine at 200mg improves attention and reduces anxiety without sedation. Lion's mane mushroom is the second strongest candidate, with research showing it stimulates nerve growth factor (NGF) production, supporting neuroplasticity and long-term cognitive function.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are focus gummies better than coffee for concentration?</summary>
      <p>Focus gummies and coffee work through completely different mechanisms. Coffee provides alertness via caffeine's adenosine receptor blockade, which prevents drowsiness but can also cause anxiety, jitters, and an energy crash. Focus gummies containing L-theanine and lion's mane promote calm concentration through alpha brain wave modulation and neurotrophic factor support — without stimulant side effects. Many users find that combining L-theanine with a small amount of caffeine (100mg) produces superior focus to either alone, a synergy documented in a 2008 study in <em>Nutritional Neuroscience</em>.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long do focus gummies take to work?</summary>
      <p>Ingredients in focus gummies have different onset times. L-theanine produces measurable increases in alpha brain wave activity within 30 to 40 minutes of ingestion. Alpha-GPC can improve attention within 1 to 2 hours. Lion's mane mushroom, which works by stimulating NGF production, requires consistent daily use over 2 to 4 weeks before cognitive improvements are typically noticeable. For immediate focus needs, choose a gummy with L-theanine or alpha-GPC. For long-term cognitive support, lion's mane-based formulas offer compounding neuroplasticity benefits over time.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can I take focus gummies with coffee?</summary>
      <p>Yes, and the combination may actually be beneficial. L-theanine, the most common active ingredient in focus gummies, has been shown to complement caffeine by smoothing out the stimulant's edge. A 2008 study in <em>Nutritional Neuroscience</em> found that the L-theanine plus caffeine combination improved both speed and accuracy of attention-switching tasks better than either compound alone. The L-theanine counteracts caffeine's tendency to cause jitters and anxiety while preserving its alertness benefits. A typical effective ratio is 200mg L-theanine with 100mg caffeine — roughly one focus gummy plus one cup of coffee.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Are nootropic focus gummies safe for daily use?</summary>
      <p>The ingredients in most focus gummies — L-theanine, lion's mane, B-vitamins — have strong safety profiles for daily use. L-theanine has been used safely in doses up to 400mg daily in clinical trials lasting 8 weeks or more. Lion's mane has been consumed as a food and supplement in East Asia for centuries with no documented serious adverse effects. Alpha-GPC at 300 to 600mg daily has been used safely in cognitive decline studies lasting up to 6 months. However, focus gummies containing stimulants like caffeine or synephrine should be cycled to prevent tolerance buildup. Always check the full ingredient list and consult your physician if you take prescription medications.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What are alpha brain waves and why do they matter for focus?</summary>
      <p>Alpha brain waves oscillate at 8 to 12 Hz and are associated with a state of calm, relaxed alertness — the optimal mental state for sustained concentration, creative problem-solving, and learning. When alpha waves are dominant, the brain is focused but not stressed, which reduces cognitive fatigue and improves information retention. L-theanine is the most effective natural compound for promoting alpha wave production, working within 30 to 40 minutes of ingestion. Meditation also increases alpha waves, but L-theanine achieves a similar neurological state without requiring a dedicated daily practice.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is NGF and how does lion's mane affect it?</summary>
      <p>Nerve Growth Factor (NGF) is a protein essential for the growth, maintenance, and survival of neurons. It plays a critical role in neuroplasticity — the brain's ability to form new neural connections and adapt to new information. Lion's mane mushroom (<em>Hericium erinaceus</em>) contains hericenones and erinacines, compounds that stimulate NGF synthesis in the brain. A 2009 study in <em>Phytotherapy Research</em> found that 3g of lion's mane daily for 16 weeks significantly improved cognitive function in adults aged 50 to 80 with mild cognitive impairment. The effects were maintained only during active supplementation, reverting after discontinuation.</p>
    </details>

